               <p>Court to Rowley. Are you sure that the person now on trial, was the same person that was sworn under the name of 
               <persName id="t17850914-185-person1675">
                  Mary
                   Graham
               <interp inst="t17850914-185-person1675" type="surname" value="Graham"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850914-185-person1675" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850914-185-person1675" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ? - Yes.</p>
               <p>You have heard Mr. Hodgson, the shorthand writer, repeat now, what she swore on the trial, is it true that this conversation passed at Guildhall, in the hearing of the prisoner, or of any other person? - No my Lord.</p>
               <p>Did you ever say you would make forty pounds of the prisoner? - Never in my life.</p>
               <p>Nor to that effect? - No.</p>
               <p>Do you know Hart? - Yes.</p>
               <p>Did Hart ever tell you, or Mr. Ambler the prosecutor in your presence, to swear plump against Gosling, or else he would not be fully committed? - No, never any such thing, nor any thing to the same purport, nor I did not know Mr. Hart at this time.</p>
               <p>Did any person tell you then, to swear plump against Gosling? - No person whatever.</p>
               <p>Had you any conversation with the prisoner's mother? - No, I never spoke to her.</p>
               <p>You do not remember her begging you not to swear her child's life away? - No, my Lord, I do not remember any such thing.</p>
               <p>Did you answer her, that you would make forty pounds of him, and that you only wanted the reward? - Never in my life.</p>
